{
  "text": "First, we create a target group. This defines which instances will receive traffic from the load balancer. We're using instance targets, meaning we'll register EC2 instances directly. The target group is configured for HTTP traffic on port 80, and it's associated with our VPC. We configure health checks that ping the root path every 30 seconds. If an instance fails two consecutive health checks, it's marked unhealthy and traffic stops routing to it. Once it passes health checks again, traffic resumes. This is like failing health checks.",
